items.name: Brixel - Three flavors
items.description:
Brixel Mixes are a collection of 3 mixes between my latest checkpoint Nendo and PixelWorld's PixelMix-v2.

Since PixelMix has never been published, this is currently the only way to have a small taste of it (kind of) !

I have long been a fan of PixelWorld's style and this collaboration makes me extremely happy and proud. Before going into the details of the 3 mixes here's what you can expect from all 3 flavors:

  • Good ethnicities diversity

  • Razor-sharp details

  • A good understanding of Natural Language prompting and booru prompting

  • Gorgeous results with any VAE of your choice (I personally like Color101 , PixelWorld recommends this one from StabilityAI)

The 3 flavors go as follows:

Brixel Brain

This is carefully mixed by me to take the parts I love the most about PixelMix and make them stand out more in my Nendo outputs. Overall what you get is a slightly more sharp picture and PixelMix signature eyes stand out a bit more on top of giving you a bit more anime style.

Brixel Pixel

This was mixed by PixelWorld himself to do the exact opposite of Brixel Brain: Take what he loves the most out of Nendo and emphasize it in his PixelWorld's model. It still tilts towards Anime but with an absolute majestic touch of realism to it. It's still super sharp and clear.

Brixel Core

This is a 50/50 perfect mix of Brixel Brain and Brixel Pixel, get the best of both worlds!

Credits

  • MeinaMix weights can be found in all 3 flavors so if you use any of these checkpoints make sure to follow their license as well

  • PixelWorld. He took me in his Discord and shared a lot of tips with me, I have learned a lot from him and forever grateful he let me share this with you guys.

items.name: Hypernet Exterior Design, GDM Style, Luxury and Modern, House / Building Architecture
items.description:
This is the ultimate Hypernetwork for Luxury Modern Exterior Architecture Design trained on the style of GDM with 30k steps, 650 images (captioned and tokened). This hypernet is designed to be flexible and mixed into prompts instead of having a dedicated checkpoint. Has been thoroughly tested to find the best Steps/CFG/Weight/Training Combination.

***Remember to adjust the weight of the hypernet as needed. This Hypernet is very strong so I highly recommend you start at 0.30 weight and go as low as 0.05 as needed, if you see artifacts/issues***

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS SD 1.5:

Steps: 60

CFG: 15

Prompt Trigger Words: "<hypernet:gdmexthn-30000:0.30> luxury modern house "

Add words like design, home, building, etc and rotate the words around.

Tip#1: Try to use the above Steps and CFG settings first and tweak from there. I think 50 steps may be the minimum acceptable quality. CFG 13 is minimum and after 18, will be a hit or a miss. But you can try other settings to fit your needs.

Tip#2: Using prompt "<hypernet:gdmexthn-30000:0.30> luxury modern house " works best to trigger the look, then add your own prompt to spice up the picture! Of course, remember to check/modify the 0.30 weight as needed!!!!

As a favor, please let me know your thoughts, feedback and give a review rating. I would truly appreciate it!

items.name: Lauren Cohan (Maggie from The Walking Dead TV Show)
items.description:
This LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting 68 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

From my experience it runs best with Edge Of Realism, pirsusEpicRealism, epicDiffusion ,RealisticVision, CyberRealistic, Deliberate checkpoints, among others, although I think it will be just fine in other SD 1.5 models as well.

CFG scale should be between 4-7.

LyCORIS weights should be between 1-1.4

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.

items.name: Peter Pan - Wendy Darling
items.description:
If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) for the sake of motivation and stuff ;D

For usage guidance, look into the About this version box for more information and click on Show more to get all trigger words and combinations (The trigger words in the Details box are a pain to manage).

Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

About

Well, Wendy is the byproduct of my previous Tinkerbell Lora, it just happens that now I had the time to train the model.

Training

As I said, this LoRa is the by-product of the Tinkerbell Lora, so I didn't fine-tune my collecting process (for other LoRas I sometimes rewind the video frame perfectly to get exactly the frame I want, but here I just paused and if the frame looked okish, I collected it ^^ Result: 33 pictures for training, which is plenty considering that the only variety Wendy shows is whether she's wearing a feather headband or not... Nevertheless, the result is quite nice :) The only problem: due to the fact that she wears her blue nightgown all the time its a bit harder to put some other clothes on her that are not... blue
